00:04:30.190 --> 00:04:35.950
all the way back in the 1950s,
"How to Lie With Statistics."

00:04:35.950 --> 00:04:37.660
Everyone should read this.

00:04:37.660 --> 00:04:39.460
It was written by Darrell Huff.

00:04:39.460 --> 00:04:42.760
It's sold over two million
copies since the mid-'50s.

00:04:42.760 --> 00:04:45.200
It's still in print.

00:04:45.200 --> 00:04:46.260
And here's what he says.

00:04:46.260 --> 00:04:49.610
Basically, you can
take this to the bank.

00:04:49.610 --> 00:04:52.760
"Rarely you live through a
day without having statistics

00:04:52.760 --> 00:04:56.340
forced on you by radio,
television, billboard,

00:04:56.340 --> 00:04:57.540
or newspaper.

00:04:57.540 --> 00:05:00.250
This book will keep
you from being fooled.

00:05:00.250 --> 00:05:03.480
Read it and discover which
statistic is the phony."

00:05:03.480 --> 00:05:06.800
And by the way, you almost
cannot pick up a newspaper,

00:05:06.800 --> 00:05:09.910
and you will not see some
example of rigged statistics.

00:05:09.910 --> 00:05:12.500
It may involve
school grades, maybe

00:05:12.500 --> 00:05:16.920
even involve how many ships
are in the US military,

00:05:16.920 --> 00:05:23.100
how many Special Forces
are really in Iraq,

00:05:23.100 --> 00:05:24.743
because they don't
count the number who

00:05:24.743 --> 00:05:27.740
are going to go on rotation,
so they leave out 1,000.

00:05:27.740 --> 00:05:31.750
That's another way of
rigging statistics.

00:05:31.750 --> 00:05:34.000
And I love this
quote by Disraeli,

00:05:34.000 --> 00:05:35.990
the Victorian prime
minister of England.

00:05:35.990 --> 00:05:39.470
He said, "There are three kinds
of lies-- lies, damn lies,

00:05:39.470 --> 00:05:40.740
and statistics."

00:05:40.740 --> 00:05:44.590
And then the famous H.G. Wells
said, "Statistical thinking

00:05:44.590 --> 00:05:47.064
one day will be as necessary
for efficient citizenship

00:05:47.064 --> 00:05:48.480
as the ability to
read and write."

00:05:48.480 --> 00:05:51.300
Well, that's never
happened, never will happen.

00:05:54.300 --> 00:05:58.540
Always remember, whenever you
look at statistics, a contract,

00:05:58.540 --> 00:06:01.080
whatever's handed you in
the form of statistics,

00:06:01.080 --> 00:06:04.250
the presenter has
the upper hand.

00:06:04.250 --> 00:06:06.230
Everyone has a bias.

00:06:06.230 --> 00:06:09.160
So the Department of Labor
has a bias in keeping down

00:06:09.160 --> 00:06:10.580
the inflation rate.

00:06:10.580 --> 00:06:13.510
The inflation rate,
they claim, is 2%.

00:06:13.510 --> 00:06:15.100
It's nowhere near 2%.

00:06:15.100 --> 00:06:17.150
I wish Janet Yellen
could come here

00:06:17.150 --> 00:06:20.590
for 30 seconds, the head of
the Federal Reserve, and I say,

00:06:20.590 --> 00:06:22.370
I don't think you eat food.

00:06:22.370 --> 00:06:23.495
I don't think you pay rent.

00:06:23.495 --> 00:06:25.700
You don't have any
medical expense.

00:06:25.700 --> 00:06:27.730
You don't have any
tuition expense,

00:06:27.730 --> 00:06:30.740
