Software is an
immediate expense.

00:45:20.860 --> 00:45:24.650
Most large companies
don't capitalize software,

00:45:24.650 --> 00:45:32.320
but if you really need a
jolt in earnings, you defer,

00:45:32.320 --> 00:45:35.090
you'll amortize the software.

00:45:35.090 --> 00:45:40.750
And Enron is a great example,
selling at 100 times earnings.

00:45:40.750 --> 00:45:43.424
If they didn't capitalize
that dime of software,

00:45:43.424 --> 00:45:45.840
the entire gain-- you've got
