Cash flow.

00:46:14.880 --> 00:46:18.880
What that is, that's the
best definition of cash flow.

00:46:18.880 --> 00:46:23.140
Warren Buffett makes
fun out of non-GAAP

00:46:23.140 --> 00:46:28.280
and all these other
numbers they come up with.

00:46:28.280 --> 00:46:30.434
Here again, lying
with statistic.

00:46:30.434 --> 00:46:32.100
You'll read in "The
Wall Street Journal"

00:46:32.100 --> 00:46:35.440
day after day now bigger
and bigger gap between GAAP

00:46:35.440 --> 00:46:38.580
and adjusted earnings,
which may not include

00:46:38.580 --> 00:46:41.300
the compensation on workers.

00:46:41.300 --> 00:46:46.220
They may leave out
what is recurring.

00:46:46.220 --> 00:46:49.700
I mean, what is recurring,
they'll emphasize.

00:46:49.700 --> 00:46:52.880
What's non-recurring,
