00:48:52.892 --> 00:48:54.350
and the price-earning
ratio will go

00:48:54.350 --> 00:48:58.240
higher earlier, but as the
price-earning ratio levels off,

00:48:58.240 --> 00:49:01.250
which it has to do, that's when
they start paying dividends,

00:49:01.250 --> 00:49:03.960
and the dividends
themselves can be a bonanza.

00:49:03.960 --> 00:49:07.530
Now, the stock market,
when you look at how much

00:49:07.530 --> 00:49:10.890
the stock market's
gone up, the Dow Jones,

